Sophism of War Criminal - KCNA News Analyst's Article - 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- U.S. President Bush, addressing presidential election campaign rallies, has tried to justify the U.S. invasion of Iraq and even described it as an "exceptional success".
 He, in the hope of pulling up his popularity even a little, is portraying the internationally recognized crime of war as an "exceptional success". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is clearly proved by the horrible consequences caused by the war that the invasion was, in the long run, a war of aggression and plunder and an undisguised state terrorism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The main reason of the U.S. invasion of Iraq was to "eliminate weapons of mass destruction" which had been non-existent in the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S., which has stockpiled the largest arsenal of weapons of mass destruction in the world and is still developing and using such weapons, attacked Iraq, a sovereign state, allegedly to "eliminate WMD". This is a grave challenge to world peace. It is more serious that the U.S. attacked Iraq, ignoring the United Nations and the international community standing against the war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is for Iraq's oil and the domination of the Middle East that the U.S. killed tens of thousands of civilians and destroyed peaceful towns and villages in Iraq with an intensive missile strike and indiscriminate bombing. The U.S. forces even used some 1,700 tons of depleted uranium bullets during the war, causing radioactive pollution in the whole of the country and incurable diseases among people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. abuses of Iraqi detainees astonished the international community as they are the worst violation of human rights. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
When Bush was busy with the election campaign, the U.S. occupation troops bombed towns of Iraq and killed a large number of civilians under the pretext of quelling "riot forces". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The invaders have deserved punishment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More than 1,000 U.S. troops have been killed and some 5,000 wounded by attacks of Iraqi resistance forces. The number of suicides, mattoids and deserters has steadily increased among the U.S. troops mobilized in the unethical war of aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Foreign media say that the U.S. has sunk into the abyss of the "second Vietnamese War" where the "door of the hell is always open". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Murder, arson, destruction, plunder and ceaseless bloodshed -- that is just the "exceptional success" brought by Bush from the Iraqi war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world public brands the Bush administration wrecking world peace with the homicidal policy of aggression and hegemony as a group of war criminals.

Joint Seminar Held in Russia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- A joint seminar was held at Moscow State University of Russia on September 15 on the occasion of the 56th anniversary of the foundation of the DPRK.
 Alexandr Kovalyov, chairman of the Association of Scientists for the Study of Human Affairs in the Present World, in a speech at the seminar said that the holiday of the Korean people who are maintaining their faith, system and idea is a common holiday of the world progressive people and all the Russian figures aspiring after socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people have dynamically advanced along the road of victory since the foundation of the DPRK, he said, adding that the United States dares not provoke the Korean people, and Japan and south Korea feel overawed by them as leader Kim Jong Il, the successor to President Kim Il Sung, is pursuing the Songun policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Alexandr Vorontsov, vice-chairman of the Association for the Study of the Juche Idea and DPRK's Policy, Economy and Culture, in a speech said that no moves of the U.S. and its followers to isolate and stifle the DPRK, pursuant to the hostile policy toward it, can ever dampen the ardent desire of the Korean people for the reunification of the country. He extended sincerest salute to all the Korean people who are triumphantly advancing under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il.

S. Korean Buddhists Call for Repeal of SL 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- Members of Buddhist organizations including co-representatives of the south Korean Buddhist Human Rights Committee Jin Kwan, Ji Won and Han Sang Bom on September 16 made public an appeal titled "Let's all Buddhists come out to get the Security Law abolished".
 Social democracy cannot be achieved nor can the peace and stability of the nation be attained unless the SL is scrapped, the appeal said, stressing: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The repeal of the SL is the only way of setting right the spirit of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is high time that all the Buddhists rallied closely in the fight for the repeal of the SL, the appeal said, calling upon them to turn out and get the evil law torn up with their practical struggle.

U.S. "War against Terrorism" Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- The "war against terrorism" launched by the United States after the Sept. 11 incident is a horrible criminal act of sparking a vicious cycle of terrorism and retaliation and driving the world into war, disorder and disaster. Rodong Sinmun Wednesday says this in a signed article . It goes on:
 The Afghan war launched by the U.S. under the pretext of "retaliation" against the Sept. 11 incident was a war to conquer the world in the 21st century and a prelude to the contemporary form of "crusade." The Bush forces' much publicized "war against terrorism" is not aimed at U.S. security and world peace as claimed by them but a war of aggression to seize areas of strategic importance in the world and establish military domination over them.  The Iraq war ignited by the U.S. in the wake of the start of the Afghan war was a war that crudely violated the independence of a sovereign state and a war to plunder strategic resources as it laid bare the aggressive, bestial and predatory nature of U.S. imperialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A vicious cycle of terrorism and retaliation is going on in Iraq, Afghanistan and other regions of the world as a consequence of the U.S. "war against terrorism." This is causing bloodshed and leaving the world uneasy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Bush group is working hard to round off its brigandish "strategy of preemptive attack" for escalating this war and speeding up the reorganization and redeployment of its armed forces according to the strategy, far from owning great responsibility for the above-mentioned consequences. It was so arrogant as to divide the world into a group standing on the side of the U.S. and the other group siding with "terrorism" as they pleased. It threatens that it does not rule out even the use of nuclear weapons against the anti-U.S. independent countries. The Bush warlike forces had already revealed their sinister intention to escalate their "anti-terrorist war" worldwide by listing the DPRK, Iran and Iraq as an "axis of evil." They are stepping up the preparations for the second Korean war at the last phase after singling out the DPRK as the next target of their attack after the Iraqi war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Increasing the national defence capability provides the best way of frustrating the U.S. moves for aggression and war and defending the sovereignty and security of the country.

Ending U.S. Imperialists' Occupation of S. Korea Urged 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- The Korean nation should put an end to the U.S. imperialists' occupation of south Korea and it is the only way to get rid of the misfortunes and disgrace of the nation, says Rodong Sinmun Wednesday in a signed article.
 The U.S. forces crawled into south Korea with the defeat of Japanese imperialism in 1945. It sought to rule the whole of Korea. But, failing in this attempt, they placed south Korea under its military occupation in a brigandish way. This was an illegal act of aggression which can never be justified with any subterfuge. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists' occupation of south Korea is the root cause of all the misfortunes and sufferings of the Korean people. It led to a war of aggression that brought mass killings and indiscriminate destruction in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the occupation, the U.S. imperialists committed murder, looting and anti-human crimes previously unknown against the south Korean people. With south Korea left under the U.S. imperialists' occupation, the people there can never be freed from the misfortunes, sufferings and death. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. forces present in south Korea are the main obstacle to the Korean nation's cause of independent reunification. 
 It is because of the obstructions of the U.S. imperialist aggression forces that the turning phase of reunification opened by the publication of the historic July 4 joint declaration was reversed and the inter-Korean agreement and joint declaration of denuclearization adopted with so much efforts became dead letters as soon as they came into effect. It is nobody's secrecy that the desire of the participants in the April 19 popular uprising was dashed and the popular uprising in Kwangju was brutally suppressed by the U.S. imperialist aggressors. It was again those aggression forces that put a block on the way of reunification by staging such massive joint military exercises as "Team Spirit", "Foal Eagle", "RUSOI" and "Ulji Focus Lens" whenever the spirit of Koreans for reunification rose to a new tide. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now the Korean people's advance toward independent reunification to implement the June 15 joint declaration under the banner of the Korean nation-first spirit has stumbled upon trials and difficulties. And this is also attributable to the U.S. imperialists' occupation of south Korea and their anti-reunification acts of interference.

Pyongyang Chamber of Commerce 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- The Pyongyang Chamber of Commerce of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea is conducting brisk activities of service and cooperation with local and foreign trade and investment organizations.
 In close contact with the national committees under the International Chamber of Commerce (ICC), commercial chambers and trade centers of other countries and international economic and trade organizations, it is engaged in trade, investment, transport, arbitration and service. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chamber, which was formed in March Juche 89 (2000) with the backing or joining of 12 local and foreign banking and trade organs, has more than 20 fellow companies now. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has the Trade Information Service Committee, the Trade Exhibition Committee, the International Transportation Committee, the Financial Committee and the Arbitration Committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ICC admitted the Pyongyang Chamber of Commerce to it at the 33rd World Congress held in May 2000. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 General secretary of the chamber Ri Song Un told KCNA that the chamber's efforts for establishing fresh and fair international trade relations will draw great interest of commercial chambers, trade and banking organs of countries and promote close contact and cooperation among them.

Wreaths Laid before Statues of Kim Jong Suk
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were laid before the bust of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk at the Revolutionary Martyrs' Cemetery on Mt. Taesong Wednesday on the occasion of her 55th death anniversary.
 Standing before the bust was a wreath from Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea, chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission and supreme commander of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participating in the wreath-laying ceremony were senior officials of the Party, the state and the army, chairpersons of the friendly parties, members of the Cabinet, senior officials of party and military organs, power bodies, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions, anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters, servicepersons, working people and youth and students in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Overseas Koreans staying in the socialist homeland were also present there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amidst the playing of the wreath-laying music, wreaths were placed before her bust in the name of the WPK Central Committee, the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly and the DPRK Cabinet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also laid there were bouquets and wreaths in the name of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces, working people's organizations, ministries, national institutions, KPA units, scientific, educational, public health and media institutions, the National Joint Organization of the Korean Children's Union, the Party and power bodies, factories and farms in the city, delegations and homeland-visiting groups of overseas Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbons of the wreaths were words "The revolutionary exploits of the anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk will be immortal!". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants observed a moment's silence in memory of her noble revolutionary life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the military attaches' corps here laid a wreath before her bust. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Floral baskets in the name of ministries and national institutions, the Party and power bodies, working people's organizations, KPA units, factories, enterprises, farms and schools in Pyongyang and local areas and bouquets were placed before her statues in Kim Jong Suk County, Ryanggang Province, and Hoeryong City, North Hamgyong Province, and at Kim Jong Suk University of Navy and Kim Jong Suk General Military Academy on the same day.
